    <h1>Swarojgaar Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>At Swarojgaar, we are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our online job portal services.</p>

    <div class="highlight">
        <h2>1. Information We Collect:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> When you register on Swarojgaar, we may collect your name, email address, contact number, address, educational qualifications, work experience, skills, and other relevant information to create your profile and provide personalized services.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Information:</strong> We collect information about how you interact with our platform, such as your IP address, device information, browser type, pages visited, and actions taken.</li>
            <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> We use cookies to enhance your browsing experience, track preferences, and gather usage data. You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="highlight">
        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Providing Services:</strong> We use your information to match you with job opportunities, communicate with employers/recruiters, and facilitate the job application process.</li>
            <li><strong>Personalization:</strong> We personalize your experience based on your profile, preferences, and interactions to improve job recommendations and user satisfaction.</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> We analyze usage patterns and trends to enhance our services, troubleshoot issues, and improve performance.</li>
            <li><strong>Communications:</strong> We may send you newsletters, updates, job alerts, and promotional offers based on your preferences. You can opt out of marketing communications anytime.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="highlight">
        <h2>3. Information Sharing:</h2>
        <p>Your profile information may be shared with employers/recruiters when you apply for jobs or express interest in opportunities.</p>
        <p>We may also engage third-party service providers to assist with platform operations, analytics, marketing, and customer support. These providers are bound by confidentiality and security obligations.</p>
        <p>We may disclose information when required by law, legal process, or to protect our rights, property, and safety or that of others.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="highlight">
        <h2>4. Data Security:</h2>
        <p>We employ industry-standard security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, misuse, alteration, or loss.</p>
        <p>However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="highlight">
        <h2>5. Your Rights:</h2>
        <p>You can access, update, or correct your personal information by logging into your account settings.</p>
        <p>You can also request a copy of your data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format or request deletion of your account and associated data, subject to legal and contractual obligations.</p>
    </div>

    <footer class="highlight">
